6. Navigation State Transitions
Employee Lifecycle States
CREATED → ONBOARDING_IN_PROGRESS → ACTIVE → EXIT_REQUESTED → EXITED
State Flow Rules:
CREATED → ONBOARDING only via HR trigger
ONBOARDING → ACTIVE only when all tasks completed
ACTIVE → EXIT_REQUESTED via manager/HR action
EXIT_REQUESTED → EXITED only after full offboarding workflow
7. API Navigation Flow (Backend Routing)
POST   /employees/create
POST   /workflow/onboard
POST   /workflow/offboard
GET    /employees/{id}
POST   /access/grant
POST   /access/revoke
GET    /audit/logs
8. Error Navigation Paths
Error Condition	Navigation Outcome
Unauthorized access	Redirect to login
Invalid workflow state	Show error + rollback
Missing employee data	Return to form
IAM failure	Queue retry job
Access denied	Show 403 page
9. Navigation Performance Rules
Dashboard load < 2 sec
Workflow pages < 3 sec
API responses < 300 ms
Lazy loading for logs and history
Pagination for employee lists
10. UX Navigation Principles
Role-based visibility (no clutter)
Minimal clicks to complete onboarding
Clear status indicators (Pending / Active / Completed)
Breadcrumb navigation for workflows
Real-time status updates
